==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English, derived from Old English ''[[braegen]]'' and ''[[bregen]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-brain.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪn|-eɪn]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# That part of the [[central nervous system]] of an [[animal]] located in the [[skull]] which is responsible for [[perception]], [[cognition]], [[attention]], [[memory]], [[emotion]], and [[action]].
# An [[intelligent]] person.
#:''He was a total '''brain'''.''
# {{cattag|English pluralia tantum}} A person who provides the intelligence required for something.
#:''The '''brains''' behind the scheme''
# (''in plural'' '''brains''') [[Intellect]].
#:''He has a lot of '''brains'''.''
# By analogy with a human brain, the part of a [[machine]] or [[computer]] that performs [[calculation]]s.
#:''The computer's '''brain''' is capable of millions of calculations a second.''

